{"word":"οὐλόμενος","slug":"οὐλόμενος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οὐλόμενος</b></el> <el>(οὐλόμενος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>aor2 <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> of <a href='S:ὄλλυμι'><el>ὄλλυμι</el></a>, used as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>destructive, baneful</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>fatalis</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>unhappy, undone, lost</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>perditus</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}